Researchers have observed the brightest flare-up yet seen from the black hole at the heart of our Milky Way galaxy.

As supermassive black holes go, Sagittarius A* is relatively quiet, giving off roughly as much energy as the sun - in spite of the fact it is some 4billion times as big.

About once a day, however, it emits a burst of light - a phenomenon scientists have been keen to investigate to get a better understanding of how black holes evolve.

